Make the equation using all of the variables, adjust scientific notation.

equation <- child.pov.2016 ~ rural + urban + lnmanufacturing + lnag + 
  lnretail + lnhealthss + lnconstruction + lnlesshs + 
  lnunemployment + lnsinglemom + lnblack + lnhispanic + 
  lnuninsured + lnincome_ratio + lnteenbirth + lnunmarried

options(scipen = 5)

Run a simple OLS to test relationship between child poverty and variables in dataset.

ols <- lm(equation, data=va_pov)
summary(ols)

fips <- county.fips
fips.codes <- separate(data = fips, col = polyname, into = c("state", "county"), sep = ",")
va_fips <- subset(fips.codes, state=="virginia", select=fips)

virginia <- maps::map(database = "county", regions = "virginia", fill=T, plot=F)
va_sp = map2SpatialPolygons(virginia,va_fips$fips,CRS("+proj=longlat"))
#library(sf)
se_shp <- st_read(file.path("./data/se_counties/se_counties.shp"))
## Reading layer `se_counties' from data source 
##   `/Users/HannahAlloway/Documents/APSU/Fall2023/AdvDataAna/ADA.Assignment.SpatialReg/data/se_counties/se_counties.shp'

## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -95.76748 ymin: 24.95638 xmax: -73.89775 ymax: 42.50936
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
va_sf <-  se_shp %>% subset(STATE_NAME == "Virginia")

#library(spdep)
neighb.data <- poly2nb(va_sf, queen=T)
## although coordinates are longitude/latitude, st_intersects assumes that they
## are planar
cont.neighb <- nb2listw(neighb.data,style="W", zero.policy = TRUE)

Now to use a Moran’s Correlation Test designed for regression residuals to examines the residuals of the OLS regression using the spatial relationship matrix.

lm.morantest(ols, cont.neighb)
## 
##  Global Moran I for regression residuals
##

## model: lm(formula = equation, data = va_pov)
